--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Usage of JPsiFitter.C and ScaleFactors.C (Maximiliano.Sioli@CERN.CH)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

JPsiFitter.C

It takes ntuples (or histograms) from TP tool, fit signal and background and produces 1D/2D efficiency histos.
These histos are then plotted and compared using ScaleFactors.C

     JPsiFitter(TString dataSample, TString probeType, TString muType)

where:

     dataSample = dataC, dataDE, mc50, mc50-np (exp data, mc with prompt j/psi, mc with non-prompt j/psi)
     probeType = IDProbes, CaloProbes, MSProbes
     muType = LooseMuons, MediumMuons, TightMuons

Main parameters and switches:

     bool verbose
     bool massPlots 
     bool makeEPSPNGfiles
     bool useTree

e.g. RUN LIKE:

     root -b -q 'JPsiFitter.C("dataDE","IDProbes","MediumMuons")'
     root -b -q 'JPsiFitter.C("dataDE","CaloProbes","MediumMuons")'
     root -b -q 'JPsiFitter.C("dataDE","IDProbes","TightMuons")'
     root -b -q 'JPsiFitter.C("dataDE","CaloProbes","TightMuons")'
     root -b -q 'JPsiFitter.C("dataDE","MSProbes_ID","IDTracks")'

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ScaleFactors.C

It makes comparisons (ratios) between efficiency histograms.

      ScaleFactors(TString dataSample1 , TString probeType1, TString dataSample2, TString probeType2, TString muType)

where:

      dataSample1/2 = dataC_50ns, dataDE_25ns, mc_50ns, mc_25ns
      probeType1/2 = IDProbes, CaloProbes, MSProbes, TruthProbes_Muon
      muType = MediumMuons, TightMuons

e.g. RUN LIKE:

     root -l 'ScaleFactors.C("data","IDProbes","mc-p","IDProbes","MediumMuons")'

N.B. In case of TruthProbes, data are directly read from NTuples and not from the previous root file generated by JPsiFitter

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
